      "writtenOn": "2020-11-12T14:34:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point(s).\n\nRegardless of whether we remove flush from SkSurface though, we also need to fix the failability issue both in the public API and internally. Right now we conflate, has-there-been-an-error, did-we-flush-anything and were-the-semaphores-submitted.\n\nThe \"void GrDirectContext::flush()\" signature is particularly egregious.",
      "parentUuid": "a2a4802c_a0938865",
